<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-601-113  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 601 113.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  Oct 1990 v22 n10 p56(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>External CAD service increases efficiency, quality.andO;(computer-aided design) (Applications)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Companies now often employ document restoration scanning andcomputer-aided design (CAD) conversion firms as part of ComputerIntegrated Manufacturing (CIM) operations, thus increasingefficiency, accuracy and productivity.andP;  An example of a companythat benefits in this way is Eaton-Kenway, which designs, developsand manufactures Automated Guided Vehicles (AVGs) and Storage andRetrieval Vehicles (SRVs).andP;  Eaton-Kenway contracted with ComputerGraphics/Atlanta (CGA), a document scan/conversion and restorationservice that converts engineering documents into high resolutionraster images or completely vectorized graphic files.andP;  Anothercompany, Bowater Inc, contracted with CGA for restoration ofdeteriorated and torn drawings of piping and pumps in a newsprintmill.andP;  The work took three years, but was successfully completed,restoring badly damaged materials in a cost effective manner.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Graphics/Atlanta (Contracts)Eaton-Kenway Inc. (Contracts)Bowater Inc. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    BOW.andO;Topic:     Computer-Integrated ManufacturingComputer-aided designOutsourcingCAD-CAMEngineering Services.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>